<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880617-0040 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: General Motors Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GM FREST GMH </CO><IN> ARO TEL </IN><TEXT>   Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors Corp.'s Hughes Electronics subsidiary, said it won the right to negotiate a contract for Australia's next generation of communications satellites.    Hughes, El Segundo, Calif., said the final contract could be valued as much as $500 million. It said it beat out three other competitors to reach this round.    The final contract is expected to be awarded in June, and the first launch is set for late 1991. Hughes built Australia's national network of three communications satellites, the last of which was launched in September. </TEXT></DOC>